 knock quality of gasoline and combusion chamber
 design are the controlling factors in fuel burning. The
 hemispherical combustive chambers are being widely
 accepted as conductive to good fuel efficiency. In it
 there are no remote corners for pressure to build up and
 no sharp corners to retain the heat. However, some pro-
 visions must 'be made in high compression engines for
 creating turbulence in the charge. It has been shown
 that ia well -mixed c,harge will burn more evenly than
 one in which the suspended gasoline droplets are of
 uneven size. Tihus the innovation known as a "squish
 area" was adopted. This is a part of the combustion
 chamber with very little clearance for the piston when
a:t top dead center. As the piston approaches the
squish area, it drives the entrapped mixture out in a
jet into the main body of charge, thus creating auxiliary
turbulence.
