 the first four models shot into the cold air. One by one
 the frail 'models strained at the catapult with 'the
 force of their tiny steam engines, and one by one they
 were cut loose only to drop and sink beneath the waters
 of the river.
     In October, 1894, Aerodrome No. 5 was launched
 and maintained a flight of 'three seconds which covered
 about 35 feet. The aerodrome weighed 22 pounds
