 obtaining the mere engine power to sustain a machine
 in the air." The experiments were continued in the
 face of certain d'efeat. But a lesson had been learned:
 balance was the secret of sustained flight.
     After much thought to the necessity of proper
 moments of rotation;, a pair of tandem wings and a
 pair of crossed planes for the tail assembly was decided
