 omer -for his failures. Again, Manly insisted that the
 professor attempt one more trial. The money from the
 government plus a loan from the Smithsonian Institute
 and a great deal of the personal savings of Manly and
 Langley had already been used up. As a result of the
 bad publicity, no more money was forthcoming, and a
 final trial was never made.
     And so ended the experiments in flight by Profes-
 sor Samuel Piermont Langley. A short time after the
 failure of the fund-raising campaign for the last trial
 of Langley's man-carrying machine, the Wright broth-
 ers successfully made their flight at Kitty Hawk. When
