..on economy in national defense


"The widespread belief that there is an inherent conflict
of interest between those who put national security first
on the one hand and the taxpayer and his cost-conscious
representatives on the other is simply erroneous - except
when the level of the national security budget is at issue.
Once the budget level has been fixed, the choice of
weapons which maximizes our military capability is logi-


cally equivalent to the choice which minimizes the cost
of attaining that capability. Moreover, the weapon
characteristics so chosen are typically similar at different
budget levels. In these circumstances economy and mili-
tary effectiveness are not opposing objectives to be com-
promised: they are different but equivalent aspects of the
same national objective."
      -Charles Hitch, Head of the Economics Division


